\begin_layout Standard
On GNU/Linux Debian and Ubuntu, you can easily create a directory Private
 in your home directory.
 This directory will be encrypted using the password you use to connect
 when you start your computer.
 Just type ecryptfs-setup-private in a terminal to create it.
 You have to logout/login agan.
 You can then put the work directory of Paperwork in it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once the directory has been created, you can also store Paperwork cache
 in it:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Verbatim

$ mv ~/.local/share/paperwork ~/Private/paperwork_cache
\end_layout

